51230799.developer_response:
Hello,

Thank you for your review and honest feedback. I’m sorry to see you’re not satisfied with the game as a whole, but I would like to elaborate a bit about the game’s completion and content, especially as you didn’t play the game over the last 3 months.

First of all, you said that there’s no content to do after reaching level 100. Right from the day of Early Access launch, Gloria Victis continuously receives a steady flow of updates – at least one per week. These updates introduce fixes to bugs reported by our players, improvements requested by the Community, and new features and content.

Over the time in which you didn’t play, we applied 15 regular updates. Along many changes, they introduced:
– Player-built siege engines (and other new objects built by the players), which changed the sieges over castles a lot;
– Weekly Rankings, which allow players to compete each other in various activities even after reaching the level cap – this feature requested by Community and nicely expands the competitive content, adding to the already existing Glory and Arena rankings (former rewarding players for activity in RvRvR battles, and the latter rewarding individuals for advancing in ranked duels leaderboard);
– A new world event “Fall of the Exile”, which is a PVE raid for larger groups (with optional PVP, as it takes place in the open-world location, so other factions can access it too);
– Another new world event “Abandoned Route”, a dungeon-like content designed for groups of 5 players where you can gain a lot of valuable resources;
– Taverns to be built and upgraded by players in castles and towns controlled by their nation/guild;
– Many improvements to combat and its balance, as well as to the RvRvR balance as a whole;
– Numerous roleplay additions, like a dice game which expands the non-combat content and displaying guild emblems on shields.

These are just some features from the last 15 updates. Anyway, we don’t consider Gloria Victis a “fully created game” yet. It is still not feature complete – we say it clearly in the store description:
“Please remember that the game is currently in alpha stage and you may experience some issues or some of the features may not be implemented yet. We recommend supporting us only if you want to help us develop the game!”


Of course, as you said, the game is designed and developed in a way that it’s fully functional and playable since Early Access launch, but it’s still not the final release yet. Reason is pretty simple: while it’s a standard for MMORPGs to be created by teams of hundreds, we’re a small indie company with about 15 guys on-board, so it takes time.

Speaking of factions – this kind of open PVP everlasting confilct is one of the Gloria Victis main pillars, and guild+controlled castles are another layer of it. It’s true that Gloria Victis has a pretty strong emphasis on PVP itself, but we believe that the nations system makes it easier for new players to join the game and make an impact on the game’s world than you have in the classic open-world PVP games which primarily focus on the guild content.

Summing up, I’m wondering if you could possibly re-think if we really deserve a negative review just for the fact that the game isn’t fully completed (both feature- and content-wise) yet. We know it, and we say it clearly. We’re not a super-large team, but I believe our hard work is easily visible. We update the game every week, we’re as transparent as possible and we carefully listen to our Community. In the end, you’ve already got almost 400 hours of playtime, which is always a nice feeling for any game developer after all. :)

Have a great weekend!

Best regards,
Bartold
